=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_LinXFade2_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_bright pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 800 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally sparse.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: very_bright
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: sparse
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 800.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: -9.9484
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5795
  pitch_clarity: 50.9580
  inharmonicity: 0.0066
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -9.6479
  resonance_freq: 796.7285

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: LinXFade2 Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/LinXFade2.html
// Tags: LinXFade2, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
play({ LinXFade2.ar(FSinOsc.ar(800, 0, 0.2), PinkNoise.ar(0.2), FSinOsc.kr(1)) });
